import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    sns.histplot(data=data, x='age', kde=True, color='blue', bins=10)
    plt.axvline(data['age'].median(), color='red', linestyle='dashed', linewidth=2, label=f"Median: {data['age'].median():.2f}")
    plt.title("What is the distribution of ages in the dataset?", wrap=True)
    plt.legend()
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    sns.boxplot(data=data, y='height')
    avg_height = data['height'].mean()
    plt.axhline(avg_height, color='r', linestyle='--', label=f'Average Height: {avg_height:.2f}')
    plt.title('What is the average height of people in the dataset?', wrap=True)
    plt.legend()
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

    return plt;

import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    name_counts = data['name'].value_counts()
    ax = sns.barplot(x=name_counts.index, y=name_counts.values)
    ax.set(xlabel='Name', ylabel='Frequency')
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    plt.title('What is the most common name in the dataset?', wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
